A pensioner who killed her husband of 50 years after he was diagnosed with terminal cancer claimed today that it was an act of mercy.

A court heard Sheila Sampford plead guilty to strangling her husband 82-year-old John, who was dying from leukaemia, at their home in Milton Keynes, Buckinghamshire.

But she insisted that her motive was to end his pain, and must now face a separate hearing to determine if the murder was indeed an act of mercy.

